@massimopalmieri yes I've tested using the [Shaka reference player](https://shaka-player-demo.appspot.com/) and it worked both with the Widevine test manifests and some custom content I have access to.

To test playback I've been using the following in `main.js` (interesting that @romaincointepas has been successful using the `register-pepper-plugins` switch).

```
//You need to manually source the widevinecdmadapter.plugin and add to the dir below
var widevinePath = app.getPath('appData').concat('/YOUR-APP-NAME/WidevineCDM/widevinecdmadapter.plugin');
app.commandLine.appendSwitch('widevine-cdm-path', widevinePath);
app.commandLine.appendSwitch('widevine-cdm-version', '1.4.8.824');
```

And then one of the following in the html:

`<webview id="netflix" src="http://netflix.co.uk" plugins></webview>`

`<webview id="shaka" src="https://shaka-player-demo.appspot.com/" plugins disablewebsecurity>
</webview>`

@tommoor which platform are you on? I compiled Electron on the Mac shortly after this was merged into master and it's been working for me. I hadn't got around to building it on the other platforms.

If you've followed the above, and loaded the CDM via a standard 'register-pepper-plugins' then you won't have triggered the Key registration. To do this use 'widevine-cdm-path' ('widevine-cdm-version' is also needed but you can set it to anything from my testing).

That's detailed in the [using-widevine-cdm-plugin.md](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/docs/tutorial/using-widevine-cdm-plugin.md) docs.

Just tried the new release on OS X 10.11.2 and can successfully watch movies on Amazon Prime. 
This is the code I am using:

``` js
'use strict';

const electron = require('electron');
const path = require('path');

electron.app.commandLine.appendSwitch('widevine-cdm-path', path.join(__dirname, 'widevinecdmadapter.plugin'));
electron.app.commandLine.appendSwitch('widevine-cdm-version', '1.4.8.866');

let mainWindow = null;

electron.app.on('ready', () => {
    mainWindow = new electron.BrowserWindow({
        webPreferences: {
            plugins: true
        }
    });
    mainWindow.loadUrl('https://amazon.de');
});
```

